ce:section.ce:para:
A zinc oxide quantum dot stabilised hydrogel synthesized by solvothermal treatment of PVP in a methanol zinc electrolyte solution is reported here for the first time. This simple one-step synthesis approach did not require additional cross-linking agents and produced a firm pellet which became a soft stable transparent hydrogel following removal of unbound precursors (Fig. 1
                        ). This metallo-hydrogel possessed a remarkable water holding capacity (48.84 g water/g gel matrix) with approximately 1000 mg of hydrated gel possessing only 20 mg of solid material following oven drying at 80 °C (Fig. 2
                        A).
